featured_question.question:
Dear everyone,

I'm writing a paper about this beautiful mosque. Where can I get pictures, a map and further information about the building? Thank you in advance!

Hanna Janatka
featured_question.answer:
Established by Zainuddin Makhdum, a Muslim spiritual leader in the year 1510, the Ponnani Juma Masjid is considered as the Mecca of Muslims in Kerala. The mosque is said to have been built by a Hindu artisan, in the traditional temple architectural style of Kerala.
An outstanding feature of the Juma Masjid, apart from being built by a Hindu, is the lamp installed here which is nearly 500 odd years old. The mosque was once an important centre of Islamic philosophy and students from across the globe would sit under this oil lamp which is still kept burning to acquire knowledge. The mosque is also known as Valiya Juma Masjid.
Courtesy: native planet

featured_reviews.review_id:
Valiya Juma Masjid is an important pilgrimage site which is one of the oldest mosques. It is situated in Ponnani in Malappuram district of Kerala. Also known as Ponnani Jum'ah Masjid or Makhdum Mosque, it was built in the 16th century AD. Ponnani, once known as the "Little Mecca of Malabar" and the "Jami'at al-Azhar of Malabar", was a prominent center of Islamic learning. There are some mausoleums of the Malappuram martyrs located in the vicinity of the Mosque.

This place is prominently visited during the four-day annual festival, which is held every year in the month of April.

featured_reviews.review_id:
The significance of Cheraman Juma Majsid in the Muziris Heritage Project lies in the fact that it is the first mosque in India. Built in 629 AD by Malik Ibn Dinar it is located in the district of Thrissur in Kerala, on the Paravur-Kodungallur road.

The masjid is believed to have been renovated in the 11th century and also 300 years ago. The front portion was expanded in 1974 and further expanded in 1984.

IT WAS'NT RENOVATION, IT IS CALLED DESTRUCTION OF LEGACY

So-called renovation wouldn't mean the destruction of the ancient heritage structure. The effect of the construction resulted the destruction of the heritage mosque in the name of restoration.

The government is respondent as its archaeological department seemed to have erred, if not deliberately, in trying to remove the heritage in the name of repair/upgradation. The neighborhood (including my self) people are also equally responsible.

featured_reviews.review_id:
The mosque I recently visited left a profound impression on me. It was a place of tranquility, spirituality, and community.

Upon entering, I was struck by the stunning architecture and intricate design of the mosque. The craftsmanship and attention to detail were evident in every corner, from the beautiful geometric patterns adorning the walls to the elegant calligraphy embellishing the prayer hall.

The atmosphere inside the mosque was serene and peaceful. The soft lighting and subdued colors created a sense of serenity, fostering a calm and reflective ambiance. The absence of unnecessary distractions allowed me to focus on my prayers and personal connection with the divine.

The mosque was well-maintained and clean, reflecting the reverence and respect given to the sacred space. The staff and volunteers were welcoming, providing guidance and assistance to visitors. They were knowledgeable about the mosque's history, traditions, and rituals, and readily answered any questions I had.

During prayer times, the congregation came together, forming a sense of unity and community. It was heartwarming to see people from diverse backgrounds and cultures gathering in harmony, united in their faith. The imam's recitation of the Quran was melodic and heartfelt, enhancing the spiritual experience.

Beyond its role as a place of worship, the mosque served as a hub for community activities and engagement. It offered educational programs, lectures, and social events that promoted learning, understanding, and social cohesion among its members. This inclusive and welcoming approach fostered a sense of belonging and support within the community.

In conclusion, the mosque I visited exemplified the essence of a sacred space. Its exquisite architecture, peaceful atmosphere, and strong sense of community made it a place of solace and inspiration. I left with a deep sense of spiritual fulfillment and a desire to return. featured_reviews.review_text:
The mosque I recently visited left a profound impression on me. It was a place of tranquility, spirituality, and community.

Upon entering, I was struck by the stunning architecture and intricate design of the mosque. The craftsmanship and attention to detail were evident in every corner, from the beautiful geometric patterns adorning the walls to the elegant calligraphy embellishing the prayer hall.

The atmosphere inside the mosque was serene and peaceful. The soft lighting and subdued colors created a sense of serenity, fostering a calm and reflective ambiance. The absence of unnecessary distractions allowed me to focus on my prayers and personal connection with the divine.

The mosque was well-maintained and clean, reflecting the reverence and respect given to the sacred space. The staff and volunteers were welcoming, providing guidance and assistance to visitors. They were knowledgeable about the mosque's history, traditions, and rituals, and readily answered any questions I had.

During prayer times, the congregation came together, forming a sense of unity and community. It was heartwarming to see people from diverse backgrounds and cultures gathering in harmony, united in their faith. The imam's recitation of the Quran was melodic and heartfelt, enhancing the spiritual experience.

Beyond its role as a place of worship, the mosque served as a hub for community activities and engagement. It offered educational programs, lectures, and social events that promoted learning, understanding, and social cohesion among its members. This inclusive and welcoming approach fostered a sense of belonging and support within the community.

In conclusion, the mosque I visited exemplified the essence of a sacred space. Its exquisite architecture, peaceful atmosphere, and strong sense of community made it a place of solace and inspiration. I left with a deep sense of spiritual fulfillment and a desire to return. I would highly recommend visiting this mosque to experience its beauty, serenity, and the sense of unity it embodies.
